ORIGINAL ISSUES (for reference):

1. NAVBAR.TSX - Missing Error Handling for Logout
   Location: Line 34-37
   Issue: signOut() has no try-catch block
   Fix: Wrap signOut in try-catch and handle errors
   Example:
   const handleLogout = async () => {
     setMenuOpen(false);
     try {
       await signOut(auth);
     } catch (error) {
       console.error("Logout failed:", error);
       // Optionally show error to user
     }
   };

2. NAVBAR.TSX - Missing Accessibility Attributes
   Location: Line 91-97 (menu toggle button)
   Issue: Menu toggle doesn't have aria-expanded attribute
   Fix: Add aria-expanded={isMenuOpen} to menuToggle button
   Example:
   <button
     className={styles.menuToggle}
     onClick={() => setMenuOpen((prev) => !prev)}
     aria-label="Toggle navigation"
     aria-expanded={isMenuOpen}
   >

3. SIDEBAR.TSX - Missing Error Handling for Logout
   Location: Line 36-42
   Issue: signOut() is not awaited and has no error handling
   Fix: Make function async and add try-catch
   Example:
   const handleAuth = async () => {
     if (user) {
       try {
         await signOut(auth);
       } catch (error) {
         console.error("Logout failed:", error);
       }
     } else {
       dispatch(setAuthModalOpen(true));
     }
   };

4. SEARCHBAR.TSX - Console.error in Production Code
   Location: Line 88
   Issue: console.error should be removed or replaced with proper error logging
   Fix: Remove console.error or use proper error logging service
   Note: Error is already dispatched to Redux, console.error is redundant

5. SEARCHBAR.TSX - Missing Accessibility Label
   Location: Line 128-134 (input element)
   Issue: Search input missing aria-label for screen readers
   Fix: Add aria-label="Search for books"
   Example:
   <input
     type="text"
     placeholder="Search for books..."
     value={searchQuery}
     onChange={(e) => setSearchQuery(e.target.value)}
     className={styles.input}
     aria-label="Search for books"
   />

6. AUTHMODAL.TSX - Silent Error Handling
   Location: Multiple locations (lines 35, 49, 63, 78, 100)
   Issue: Errors are logged to console but not shown to users
   Fix: Dispatch errors to Redux state so users can see what went wrong
   Current: console.log("Login attempt:", e?.message ?? "Login failed");
   Should: dispatch(setError(e?.message ?? "Login failed"));

7. AUTHMODAL.TSX - Inconsistent Error Handling
   Location: Line 86-88 (onLogout function)
   Issue: onLogout has no error handling or loading state
   Fix: Add try-catch and loading state like other auth functions
   Example:
   const onLogout = async () => {
     dispatch(setLoading(true));
     try {
       await signOut(auth);
     } catch (e: any) {
       dispatch(setError(e?.message ?? "Logout failed"));
     } finally {
       dispatch(setLoading(false));
     }
   };

8. NAVBAR.TSX - Menu Toggle Icon Animation
   Location: CSS file (Navbar.module.css)
   Issue: Menu toggle icon doesn't animate when menu is open (should show X icon)
   Fix: Add CSS class for open state that transforms icon to X
   Add to Navbar.tsx:
   className={`${styles.menuToggleIcon} ${isMenuOpen ? styles.menuToggleIconOpen : ""}`}
   Add to CSS:
   .menuToggleIconOpen::before {
     transform: translateY(0) rotate(45deg);
   }
   .menuToggleIconOpen::after {
     transform: translateY(0) rotate(-45deg);
   }

PRIORITY ORDER:
